---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import "../styles/pages/about.css";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Kat's Kronicles." mainClass="about-page">
  <section class="about-hero" aria-labelledby="about-title">
    <div>
      <p class="about-eyebrow">Kat's Kronicles / About</p>
      <h1 class="about-title" id="about-title">A game writing archive with opinions, not roundup filler.</h1>
      <p class="about-lede">
        Kat's Kronicles is built for reviews that sit with a game after the ending and for boss essays
        that care about encounter design, pacing, and why one fight keeps living in your head.
      </p>

      <div class="about-sections">
        <article class="about-panel">
          <p class="about-panel-label">Reviews</p>
          <h2>Finished games, not first impressions</h2>
          <p>
            The review side of the archive is for complete reads on games that held up, fell apart,
            or became more interesting once the novelty wore off.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="about-panel">
          <p class="about-panel-label">Boss Features</p>
          <h2>Fight design as its own subject</h2>
          <p>
            Some encounters deserve more than a paragraph in a review. Those pieces focus on a single
            boss, what the mechanics are asking for, and whether the fight earns its reputation.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="about-panel">
          <p class="about-panel-label">Editorial Bias</p>
          <h2>Specificity over neutrality</h2>
          <p>
            The goal here is not to flatten every opinion into a scorecard. The writing leans into
            friction, taste, and the details that make a recommendation feel honest.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="about-panel">
          <p class="about-panel-label">The Archive</p>
          <h2>Built to keep older pieces readable</h2>
          <p>
            This site is structured as an archive first, so reviews and essays stay easy to browse,
            search, and revisit long after the release-week cycle is gone.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="about-card" aria-label="Site snapshot">
      <p class="about-card-label">Snapshot</p>
      <h2>What you will find here</h2>
      <p>Long-form criticism, focused encounter writeups, and an archive that is meant to be revisited.</p>

      <div class="about-card-stat">
        <strong>2 lanes</strong>
        <span>Reviews + Boss Features</span>
      </div>

      <p>
        If you want the fastest route into the site, start with the latest reviews or jump straight into
        the searchable archive.
      </p>

      <div class="about-links">
        <a class="about-link" href="/reviews/">Browse Reviews</a>
        <a class="about-link" href="/bossfeatures/">Boss Features</a>
        <a class="about-link" href="/search/">Search Archive</a>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
